strings programming -
task 1 - CODE
         string = input("enter your string:")
         length = len(string)
         middle_no = round(length//2)
         middle_letter = string[middle_no]
         print(middle_letter)

OUTPUT 
         enter your string: python
         h
         
task 2 - CODE
         string1 = input("enter first string:")
         string2 = input("enter second string:")
         len1 = str(len(string1))
         len2 = str(len(string2))
         print(string1 + len2 + string2 + len1)
OUTPUT
         enter first string: python
         enter second string: world
         python5world6

